To run the React application server, you'll need the Node.js JavaScript runtime and npm (the Node.js package manager) installed. npm is included with Node.js 

--> In Visualstudio code, Click on view and open Terminal.
--> In Terminal , type
  -npm init
  -npm install react react-dom --save
  -npm install babel-preset -env babel-preset-react
  -npm install -g parcel-bundler  
--> Create a new file 'babel.rc' in visual studio code and put following code and save the file.
    {
      "presets" : [
          "env", "react"
      ]
    }
    
